<div class="mb-requirement-container">
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14140">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> </span>
      <b>NOTE: </b> The official merit badge pamphlets are now free and
      downloadable
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Pamphlets/Photography.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        >HERE</a
      >
      or can be purchased at the
      <a href="https://www.scoutshop.org/" target="_blank ">Scout Shop.</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11407">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      Safety. Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11407 mb-requirement-id-11408">
        (a) Explain to your counselor the most likely hazards you may encounter
        while working with photography and what you should do to anticipate,
        mitigate, prevent, and respond to these hazards. Explain how you would
        prepare for exposure to environmental situations such as weather, sun,
        and water. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.coverhound.com/insurance-learning-center/is-photography-a-dangerous-career%20%20"
          target="_blank"
          >Is Photography a Dangerous Career? (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://thephotocove.com/health-and-safety-in-a-photography-studio/"
          target="_blank"
          >Health and Safety in a Photography Studio (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://loadedlandscapes.com/safety-tips-nature-photography/"
          target="_blank"
          >9 Safety Tips for Landscape and Nature Photographers (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11407 mb-requirement-id-11409">
        (b) View the Personal Safety Awareness "Digital Safety" video (with your
        parent or guardian's permission). <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/YPSAT/YT%20Mod1%20Final%20Master%20Small.mp4"
          target="_blank"
          >Digital Safety (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11426">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      Explain how the following elements and terms can affect the quality of a
      picture: <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://shotkit.com/camera-settings/" target="_blank"
        >Easy to Understand Guide to Camera Settings for Beginners (website)</a
      ><br />
      <a
        href="https://photographylife.com/common-camera-settings#camera-setup"
        target="_blank"
        >Common Camera Settings for Beginners (website)</a
      >
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11426 mb-requirement-id-11427">
        (a) Light—natural light (ambient/existing), low light (such as at
        night), and artificial light (such as from a flash) <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/FWcOshGthBI?si=Ft8P8g7G36BnSSle"
          target="_blank"
          >Golden Hour Magic: Perfect Light for Stunning Photos (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/Z9znfhFQPbE?si=iynxep4eY2ZuuzNY"
          target="_blank"
          >Artificial Lighting for Photography (So Much Easier Than You Think!)
          (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/VgT4O6CclfA?si=Gw4HDf3VeGxeE6z7"
          target="_blank"
          >Why Most Natural Light Photography is Flat (and How to Fix It)
          (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11426 mb-requirement-id-11428">
        (b) Exposure—aperture (f-stops), shutter speed, ISO <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/Edvpu_939l4?si=lFqGf0-AJuUJR-v-"
          target="_blank"
          >Iso, Shutter Speed and Aperture Explained | Exposure Basics for
          Beginners (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/V7z7BAZdt2M?si=0XATnG-lMciqFgr0"
          target="_blank"
          >Photography Basics in 10 Minutes (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11426 mb-requirement-id-11429">
        (c) Depth of field <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtube.com/shorts/98B3dvdAX6c?si=a6zX8YPAisVYAszi"
          target="_blank"
          >Depth of Field in 30 Seconds (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11426 mb-requirement-id-11430">
        (d) Composition—rule of thirds, leading lines, framing, depth <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/eImryR3yKz8?si=ITbUmVHQYD9gR72Y"
          target="_blank"
          >Basic Photography | Composition: The Only Rules You Need to Know
          (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/2uAYj6WScJQ?si=SrzE5OUdOVWWH65y"
          target="_blank"
          >Photography Composition: Master Leading Lines for Stunning Shots!
          (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtube.com/shorts/Z1Wb8ZH0uvc?si=e6TjeQIgyqaYBcUr"
          target="_blank"
          >Master the Rule of Thirds for Better Photos (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11426 mb-requirement-id-11431">
        (e) Angle of view <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/9SZy4ptc5ws?si=SfIb8MuYpZziiVaW"
          target="_blank"
          >Angle of View and Framing (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11426 mb-requirement-id-11432">
        (f) Stop action and blur motion <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/5h4J8nZn1Sw?si=n6r01F0XG_ncDOxH"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Shoot Motion Blur Photography Like a Pro (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/YtkIsA4VdRw?si=T0IV9u60N-evsqrl"
          target="_blank"
          >Photography Tips: How to Do Stop Action Photography (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11426 mb-requirement-id-11433">
        (g) Decisive moment (action or expression captured by the photographer)
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/meeqJ58eSzk?si=lxhdmU83SSLCDxvw"
          target="_blank"
          >Decisive Moment (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11438">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      Explain the basic parts and operation of a camera. Explain how an exposure
      is made when you take a picture. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/V7z7BAZdt2M?si=0XATnG-lMciqFgr0" target="_blank"
        >Photography Basics in 10 Minutes (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/BsSjEhktkzU" target="_blank"
        >Parts of a Camera (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/Ey6S3rKH_o4" target="_blank"
        >How Digital Cameras Work (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11410">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 4. </span>
      Do TWO of the following, then share your work with your counselor.
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11410 mb-requirement-id-11411">
        (a) Photograph one subject from two different angles or perspectives.
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtube.com/shorts/o5yjHn56VtE?si=XC3OvPIABX276ZtY"
          target="_blank"
          >Pro Photo Secrets: Avoid Shadows &amp; Master Poses (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11410 mb-requirement-id-11412">
        (b) Photograph one subject from two different light sources - artificial
        and natural.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11410 mb-requirement-id-11413">
        (c) Photograph one subject with two different depth of fields.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11410 mb-requirement-id-11414">
        (d) Photograph one subject with two different compositional techniques.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11419">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 5. </span>
      Photograph THREE of the following, then share your work with your
      counselor.
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11419 mb-requirement-id-11420">
        (a) Close-up of a person
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11419 mb-requirement-id-11421">
        (b) Two to three people interacting
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11419 mb-requirement-id-11422">
        (c) Action shot
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11419 mb-requirement-id-11423">
        (d) Animal shot
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11419 mb-requirement-id-11424">
        (e) Nature shot
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11419 mb-requirement-id-11425">
        (f) Picture of a person - candid, posed, or camera aware
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11415">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 6. </span>
      Describe how software allows you to enhance your photograph after it is
      taken. Select a photo you have taken, then do ONE of the following, and
      share what you have done with your counselor: <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/KR7L2oSRlwY" target="_blank"
        >PHOTO EDITING FOR BEGINNERS - 9 Simple Steps to Improve Your Photos
        (video)</a
      >
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11415 mb-requirement-id-11416">
        (a) Crop your photograph.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11415 mb-requirement-id-11417">
        (b) Adjust the exposure or make a color correction.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11415 mb-requirement-id-11418">
        (c) Show another way you could improve your picture for impact.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11434">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 7. </span>
      Using images other than those created for requirements 4, 5, and 6,
      produce a visual story to document an event to photograph OR choose a
      topic that interests you to photograph. Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11434 mb-requirement-id-11435">
        (a) Plan the images you need to photograph for your photo story.
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/UtMXpomDWlk?si=Zo4DOxTQMgshkjFA"
          target="_blank"
          >Storytelling in Photography (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11434 mb-requirement-id-11436">
        (b) Share your plan with your counselor, and get your counselor's input
        and approval before you proceed.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11434 mb-requirement-id-11437">
        (c) Select eight to 12 images that best tell your story. Arrange your
        images in order and mount the prints on a poster board, OR create an
        electronic presentation. Share your visual story with your counselor.
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/G-qyX_Ri17M?si=mFi7rrxZa1KDlNrT"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Make a PowerPoint Photo Slideshow (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11439">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 8. </span>
      Identify three career opportunities in photography. Pick one and explain
      to your counselor how to prepare for such a career. Discuss what education
      and training are required, and why this profession might interest you.
      <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/fEp_EDQE0IM?si=4IIC3sAbXyD1_6tK" target="_blank"
        >Top 10 Careers For Photographers (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a
        href="https://www.indeed.com/career-advice/finding-a-job/list-of-careers-in-photography"
        target="_blank"
        >Indeed Career Guide (website)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
